<div id="spending" class="page-break">
  <h1>Spending Analysis</h1>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Your spending requirements form the foundation of retirement planning. The following analysis breaks down your expected expenses and projects their evolution over time.</p>
    
    <h2>Annual Spending Breakdown</h2>
    
    <figure class="avoid-break" data-fig="spending-breakdown">
      {{{spendingChart}}}
      <figcaption>Figure {{figureNumber 2}}. Annual spending by category</figcaption>
    </figure>
    
    <h2>Detailed Expense Categories</h2>
    
    <h3>Monthly Recurring Expenses</h3>
    
    <table class="avoid-break">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>Monthly Amount</th>
          <th>Annual Total</th>
          <th>25-Year Total (Nominal)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Healthcare</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.health}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.health 12)}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply (multiply spending.monthly.health 12) 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Food & Groceries</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.food}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.food 12)}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply (multiply spending.monthly.food 12) 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Entertainment</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.entertainment}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.entertainment 12)}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply (multiply spending.monthly.entertainment 12) 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Shopping</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.shopping}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.shopping 12)}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply (multiply spending.monthly.shopping 12) 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Utilities</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.monthly.utilities}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.monthly.utilities 12)}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply (multiply spending.monthly.utilities 12) 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <h3>Annual Expenses</h3>
    
    <table class="avoid-break">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Category</th>
          <th>Annual Amount</th>
          <th>25-Year Total (Nominal)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Vacations & Travel</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.annual.vacations}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.annual.vacations 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Home Maintenance & Repairs</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.annual.homeRepairs}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.annual.homeRepairs 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Vehicle & Transportation</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR spending.annual.car}}</td>
          <td>{{formatEUR (multiply spending.annual.car 25)}}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <h2>Inflation Impact</h2>
    
    <div class="callout callout-warning">
      <div class="callout-title">Cost of Living Adjustments</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Expected inflation rate: {{formatPercent assumptions.inflationMean 1}} annually</li>
        <li>Today's annual spending: {{formatEUR (getTotalAnnualSpending spending)}}</li>
        <li>Projected spending in 10 years: {{formatEUR (multiply (getTotalAnnualSpending spending) 1.28)}}</li>
        <li>Projected spending in 20 years: {{formatEUR (multiply (getTotalAnnualSpending spending) 1.64)}}</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Spending Sustainability</h2>
    
    <p>Your portfolio must generate sufficient returns and withdrawals to cover:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Pre-pension period (Ages {{person.retireAge}}–{{subtract person.pensionAge 1}}):</strong> Full spending from portfolio</li>
      <li><strong>Pension period (Ages {{person.pensionAge}}–{{person.horizonAge}}):</strong> Spending minus pension income</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>